title: Three Wausau prep events to watch this week
text:
Three Wausau prep events to watch this week Tim Johnson , Daily Herald Media 9:38 p.m. CDT October 3, 2015 Buy Photo Devon Youles and the Mosinee volleyball team enter the week tied atop the Great Northern Conference standings with Medford and Tomahawk. (Photo: Dan Young/Daily Herald Media) Buy Photo CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Girls tennis: WIAA Division 1 subsectional meet, 9 a.m., Monday at SPASH — The postseason kicks off with players battling to advance to Thursday's sectional contest in Chippewa Falls. Host Stevens Point Area Senior High was the dominant team in the Wisconsin Valley Conference, and the subsectional also includes players from D. C. Everest, Marshfield, Merrill, Rhinelander, Wausau East, Wausau West and Wisconsin Rapids. Newman Catholic competes in a Division 2 subsectional at Lakeland with the chance to move on to Wednesday's sectional at Lakeland as well. 
Football: Edgar at Spencer/Columbus Catholic, 7 p.m., Friday — A nonconference matchup between two of the top teams in the area this fall. The Wildcats (6-1) are coming off their first loss of the season — a 16-8 setback to Marathon in a Marawood Conference showdown. — while the Rockets are undefeated and atop the Cloverbelt Conference. This is the fourth meeting between the two teams since 2010 and the Wildcats have won the previous three games. Last year the Wildcats beat the Rockets 28-6 in Spencer. 
Volleyball: Wisconsin Valley Conference meet No. 2, 9 a.m., Saturday at Wausau East — Merrill enters the week as the top team in the conference volleyball race with a 7-0 record in WVC games and a two-game lead over the rest of the field. The Bluejays went 3-0 in the first WVC meet and Marshfield was the other undefeated team with a 2-0 mark. The Great Northern Conference also is holding its second meet of the season Saturday in Antigo. Medford, Mosinee and Tomahawk enter the week tied for first in the GNC with 6-2 records in conference play. Read or Share this story: http://wdhne.ws/1RnWlW6 TOP VIDEOS
